nal (like a motor enable that sits HIGH or LOW for long periods) AND serve as an interrupt input for incoming pulses — the mechanisms do not collide because one is outbound static state and the other is inbound event detection, but this is a compromise that disappears the moment the enable needs to toggle during operation","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/wiring-dual-zs-x11h-for-hoverboard-robot.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[microcontrollers]]","[[wiring-integration]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},